課程概述 Course Description
       Though the course title is seminar, this course is about research methodologies. Our effort in achieving each of the objectives will assume an uneven weight distribution, which is reflective of the current and future trends in the field of social science. This course does not cover statistics. However, a solid understanding of statistics helps a lot in learning this course. We emphasize more on the conceptual reasoning. Therefore the ability to link your own domain knowledge/theories and appropriate research methods is essential in this course. Any forms of empirical supports beyond the conceptual building will be highly appreciated but not mandatory. Class participation is highly appreciated, too. Good class interactions benefit students and the instructor because it impresses the students and the instructor has a clearer idea to preside over the class during the semester. Though the course title is seminar, this course is about research methodologies. Our effort in achieving each of the objectives will assume an uneven weight distribution, which is reflective of the current and future trends in the field of social science. This course does not cover statistics. However, a solid understanding of statistics helps a lot in learning this course. We emphasize more on the conceptual reasoning. Therefore the ability to link your own domain knowledge/theories and appropriate research methods is essential in this course. Any forms of empirical supports beyond the conceptual building will be highly appreciated but not mandatory. Class participation is highly appreciated, too. Good class interactions benefit students and the instructor because it impresses the students and the instructor has a clearer idea to preside over the class during the semester.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    ~
1. To introduce both quantitative and qualitative research methods;
2. To introduce students a broad range of topics in the field of social science;
3. To give students an in-depth introduction on experiment, questionnaire design, and other modes of observations;
4. To emphasize the importance of rational thinking;
5. To help students integrate multi-discipline knowledge in this course
     

